a447518c-51e7-5ad5-add4-59e5cf2239f3,tg:rubgr:1680,e73_Descriptions,,id.desc,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,"The Blind leading the Blind, after Pieter Bruegel. Black crayon (? chalk?), 218 x 318 mm Art Institute of Chicago [...] (Photograph recieved from Jan van Gelder). Remarks: Inscriptions in ink: Brugles fecit manu pria Roma [?] (by other hand) Dedit Andreas de la p...Q (or R), Roma 1589....15. Junij. An unidentified collector's mark F.M (?) H (?) in a G all this in a circle. The Street is cut on the left and of the seventh blind person only the coat collar & beard remained. The composition is the same as in Marten van Cleve's picture in Vienna (Baldass, Jh.Z K. 1917, p. 11, fig. 7 and copies, see Glück under N° 43, & Bastelaer, Hulin de Loo, p. 377, N° 13, 13 Bis, 13 Ter)[...]",descriptive note,Nederlands,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,

column4: <content>The Blind leading the Blind, after Pieter Bruegel. Black crayon (? chalk?), 218 x 318 mm Art Institute of Chicago [...] (Photograph recieved from Jan van Gelder). Remarks: Inscriptions in ink: Brugles fecit manu pria Roma [?] (by other hand) Dedit Andreas de la p...Q (or R), Roma 1589....15. Junij. An unidentified collector's mark F.M (?) H (?) in a G all this in a circle. The Street is cut on the left and of the seventh blind person only the coat collar & beard remained. The composition is the same as in Marten van Cleve's picture in Vienna (Baldass, Jh.Z K. 1917, p. 11, fig. 7 and copies, see Glück under N° 43, & Bastelaer, Hulin de Loo, p. 377, N° 13, 13 Bis, 13 Ter)[...]</content>
